review: I used TecArmor on my S3 for years and love it--I do swap them out about every 6 months as I usually scratch the cover or it gets dirty around the edges, but they aren't meant to be permanent, so I'm good with a three pack lasting a year and a half.  They are pretty easy (though nervewracking for an OCD sort like me!) to put on, and they protect very well.  My S3 still looks brand new after nearly 3 years of use, and I am happy knowing that my S6 should fare as well, given that I got these on as quickly as possible!

review: I ordered this 'Phone Tripod, Fugetek Phone & Camera Tripod with Bluetooth Remote Shutter (51")' for review. First off let me start by saying that I thought this would work with my DSLR camera however upon receiving the Tripod with Bluetooth Remote Shutter, I realized it is only for mobile phones connecting via Bluetooth - at least in my case. My DSLR camera does not have WiFi nor Bluetooth capabilities so I can not test if it would work on cameras that have those options. With that said, the remote does work great for my Android phone. There was no issues with it connecting at all and I will definitely be using it for taking pictures with my phone. The Tripod itself is very lightweight and fairly compact and will support my heavier DSLR camera, but I am not sure I would trust it for long exposures in any kind of breeze. Overall I do like this kit for what it is, and think it has useful value.

review:

review:
This Mazoft 20mm Braided Band fits my Skagen Falster Gen 6 Smartwatch. That watch has 20mm lugs and I was excited this band fits, I’ve wanted a braided rainbow band for a while!

I have the Colorful-2 style. The colors are mostly bright, but there is a lot of white in my braid, I wish it was a bit more rainbow hued. The braid is soft and stretchy, very comfortable to wear all day long.

When I charge my watch, it’s easy to flip the band inside out so the back of my watch can sit on the charging puck.

The watch band is one length. My wrist is on the smaller end of the size range, so the adjustable buckle sits right under one of the quick release bars. That isn’t always comfortable depending on how my wrist is positioned. If I’m sitting at my desk all day, I end up taking my watch off, because the buckle bumps the top of the desk.

review:
I have no sense of direction. If I rely on memory when it comes to getting from point A to point B, it's a sure bet I'll wind up at point Q.
Using my phone for directions has become a must.
This nifty little mount holds the phone so I can glance down, and in one second, know where I am.

Yet another shortcoming is an inability to do math, and yet I like knowing if the 'economy size' really is the best bargain.
Putting this on the shopping cart when doing a serious shop allows easy access to the calculator function, as well as the shopping list.

Like many people, I'm glued to my phone and all of the information on it, and often use it like a tablet. It is so much easier when it's mounted.

review:
I have this case installed on my Samsung S9+. I usually never buy cases for my phones, but figured phones are too expensive now to leave unprotected, it's worth it even with one bad phone drop/fall.

Really satisfied with my purchase, this case is very low profile and provides added grip on the sides. The other thing it does is keeps the camera lenses elevated from any surface you put the phone on, it's really done wonders keeping the lenses cleaner and more protected. Wireless charging through the case is no problem either.

As others have mentioned, it does take some getting use to the low profile buttons, as the case is perfectly smooth on all edges, it's hard "feeling" out the buttons sometimes.

I’m very happy with this purchase, and may purchase a second if I choose to change of the look.

details: {"Package Dimensions": "6.97 x 4.57 x 0.55 inches", "Item Weight": "0.634 ounces", "Best Sellers Rank": {"Cell Phones & Accessories": 1951, "Smartwatch Screen Protectors": 57}, "Special features": "Shatter_Resistant", "Human Interface Input": "Buttons", "Form Factor": "Case", "Color": "Black/Charcoal/Silver/RoseGold", "Manufacturer": "NANW", "Date First Available": "August 18, 2020", "Brand": "NANW", "Compatible Devices": "Smartwatches", "Shell Type": "Soft"}
review:
On the plus side, this cover is inexpensive, easy to install and works. They last about two or three months before looking pretty ratty, so a four pack like I purchased will last me 8-12 months.
Two major problems I encountered were 1) hard to install with the watch on your wrist, no biggie except 2) traps water/sweat. I mean any drop near your watch will get sucked under it and trapped between the screen protector and the screen. So going back to 1, that means you take your watch off, dry it, if its sweat, rinse it off, then dry it and reinstall the screen protector.
I exercise a lot and I work a lot so I sweat a lot. I also wash my hand 8-12 times a day and sweat all day when I'm working outside. So this means taking my watch off 10-15 times a day, rinsing and drying it and putting it back on. 10-20 minutes of my day are wasted cleaning my watch. I may be the only person with this complaint but I'm looking for another screen protector, this one isn't doing it for me.

(included)", "Best Sellers Rank": {"Cell Phones & Accessories": 186562, "Cell Phone Portable Power Banks": 2580}, "Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Connectivity technologies": "USB", "Other display features": "Wireless", "Color": "sense 6+", "Manufacturer": "ROMOSS", "Date First Available": "September 7, 2018", "Brand": "ROMOSS", "Connector Type": "micro usb, usb, USB Type C", "Compatible Devices": "iPhone, Galaxy S8, iPhone X, iPhone 8, iPhone 6 Plus, iPhone 7, iPad, iPhone 4, iPhone 6", "Compatible Phone Models": "Apple iPhone X, Apple iPhone 6 Plus, Samsung Galaxy S8", "Input Voltage": "240 Volts", "Mounting Type": "Wall Mount", "Amperage": "3 Amps", "Total USB Ports": "1"}
review:
So I have a few portable chargers but most of mine are a couple years old so they don't have QC 2.0/3.0 or the new quick charging technologies. I got this product because it was listed that it had this feature so I thought I'd give it a try considering its large capacity and seemingly sturdy build. Honestly it does have both those things, its made of a dense plastic which feels heavy and sturdy in the hand. It also has a massive capacity, at 20000mAh it a can fully charge my Note 9 5 times over which is crazy.

Now for my problem with it and why I took off a star, it doesn't seem to have fast charging (at least the QC 2.0 method) which is strange considering it is listed as having it. It still seems to charge faster than other chargers which is why I didn't take off more than 1 star, but to those buying it for the QC I would avoid it.

review:
I was an Otterbox user for years. However, their case for the iPhone 12 Max Pro didn’t have a screen protector. This one does. Very similar in how it protects the phone. Only down side is that the rubber outer case doesn’t cover 100% of the back of the phone. So, if you set it down on a slick surface, it only has the rubber contact pads to prevent sliding. So, always check that the phone is not going to slip when setting it down. I like the inclusion of a phone stand…even though I likely won’t use it that often.

The only other down side is about the volume buttons. I’m used to the buttons standing out and the cover for the silent mode switch being very discrete. On this case, all 3 are tactility noticeable…so I find myself pressing on the switch cover rather than the volume up button. I’m sure that in time I’ll get used to it, but don’t be surprised if your fingers are confused for a while.
